<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/85003982/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The subject requirement of a project report and oral presentation allows students to apply Sustainable Development Objectives (SDO) strategies learnt in other subjects. More specifically, the SDO involved are the following
numbers (according to the list specified on https://www.un.org/sustainabledevelopment/es/objetivos-de-desarrollosostenible/): 6, 7, 8, 9, 11, 12 , 13 and 14).
Students will have to demonstrate in the distributed assessment activities that: they understand the main ideas of texts dealing with everyday topics (reading skills); They understand the main ideas of oral speeches (listening skills)..
They participate correctly in a conversation dealing with everyday topics (speaking and listening skills).
They write all types of texts according to the required level.
They are familiar with and respect the customs and traditions of English-speaking cultures.
They make responsible use of ICT as a tool for data collection.

Attention is paid to the SDGs (environmental respect, gender equality, poverty eradication, etc.) and coordination with other subjects in the degree programme is encouraged.
The overall assessment test in both the ordinary and extraordinary sessions will consist of a 15-minute oral test per person and a 2-hour and 45-minute written exam with questions on vocabulary, syntax and the writing of a technical text."""@es .

